Creating a website with a database and various views can be a bit complicated. Here are the basic steps you can follow to create a simple website with a database and multiple views:

1. Choose a programming language: You can use any server-side programming language, but some popular options are PHP, Python, and Ruby. In this example, we will use PHP.
2. Set up a web server: You need a web server like Apache or Nginx to run your PHP code.
3. Create a database: You can use MySQL or PostgreSQL to create your database. You can create a database using phpMyAdmin, a web-based interface for managing MySQL databases.
4. Design your database schema: Before creating a database, you need to design the schema. In this example, we will create a table called "links" with columns for title, URL, description, tags, and category.
5. Create a form to input data: You can create a form using HTML and CSS to input data into your database.
6. Use PHP to handle form submissions: When the form is submitted, you need to use PHP to insert the data into the database.
7. Create multiple views: You can create multiple views using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. In this example, we will create gallery, table, and list views.
8. Use JavaScript to switch between views: You can use JavaScript to switch between views. In this example, we will use jQuery to switch between views.
9. Use CSS to style your website: You can use CSS to style your website. You can use color-coded tags to organize and categorize your links.

Here's a sample code to help you get started:

HTML:
```php
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
	<title>My Links</title>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
	<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"></script>
	<script src="script.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
	<div class="header">
		<h1>My Links</h1>
	</div>
	<div class="content">
		<div class="view-selector">
			<button class="view-btn" data-view="gallery">Gallery</button>
			<button class="view-btn" data-view="table">Table</button>
			<button class="view-btn" data-view="list">List</button>
		</div>
		<div class="view-container">
			<!-- Gallery view -->
			<div class="view" id="gallery-view">
				<!-- Display links in gallery view -->
			</div>
			<!-- Table view -->
			<div class="view" id="table-view">
				<!-- Display links in table view -->
			</div>
			<!-- List view -->
			<div class="view" id="list-view">
				<!-- Display links in list view -->
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</body>
</html>
```
CSS:
```css
.header {
	background-color: #333;
	color: white;
	padding: 20px;
	text-align: center;
}

.content {
	margin: 20px;
}

.view-selector {
	margin-bottom: 20px;
}

.view-btn {
	background-color: #333;
	border: none;
	color: white;
	padding: 10px;
	margin-right: 10px;
}

.view-btn:hover {
	cursor: pointer;
}

.view {
	display: none;
}

.active-view {
	display: block;
}

.link {
	background-color: #f2f2f2;
	border: 1px solid #ddd;
	padding: 10px;
	margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.link:hover {
	background-color: #ddd;
}
```
